						<summary>

						<p>South wall of the <hi rend="italic">maṇḍapa</hi> in front of the same shrine.</p>						

						<p>This inscription, in Grantha characters, contains a verse in Sanskrit and it records that a certain woman named Vallī of the Śiva family, who was (as it were) Gaurī incarnate, and who was beautiful and generous, after reaching the unequalled abode of her lover, viz., the Kailāsa (i.e., the Kailāsamuḍaiya-mahādēva temple) built by Danti (i.e., Dantivarman), caused the construction of this <hi rend="italic">maṇḍapa</hi> in it for both Śiva and Śivā (i.e., Gaurī).</p>						

						</summary>
